annotation.TEXT: BGM: Fortress 2 Blue - Waiting Room

Oh, by the way, you can spin jump bounce off of Fire Bro's fireballs, but I don't think you can cape spin them. Also, be aware that the fireballs' hitboxes are more like that of a 16x16-pixel enemy (the size of a goomba).
BGM: Siren - Bright Club Lane
Uh, oh. A sequel hook? What will it be called? "Bowser Rampages Yet Again"? And will Cirno be a playable character in that one?
Now, at a certain point up ahead, the bullet cannons and Roto-Discs will be placed in such ways to make it nearly impossible to nullify all of the bullet cannons.
However, don't rush forward way too fast. You've still gotta avoid stuff, and you actually have a bit of leeway with your time limit, as this part is not very long.
Yeah, that's a lot of Cirnos, and yeah, she's probably my favorite Touhou character.
BGM: Alien vs. Predator (SNES) - Stage 4 (Space Port)
BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! TRI-FORMATION! WOO! WOO! WOO! WOO!
Is there anything hidden up above? Let me get enough speed to fly up...
Umm... Nuts to you, mushroom. I'm not gonna try any power up shuffling around those Roto-Discs.
Alright, I don't want to waste any more time. Let's just move on.
Ah, but there's still more, and with some more awesome music!
Okay, Chucks, I think the ending credits is a perfectly fine place to play sports, so play on!
That was yet another close call...
BGM: Touhou 7 - Yukari's Theme - Necrofantasia
Whoa, geez! Them Podoboos just warped right into the room!
Okay, now in this area, watch out for Bullet Bills everywhere, especially since some of these cannons do fire those evil homing bullets!
I wonder how Mario didn't end up becoming swiss cheese there...
Good thing I can cape spin boomerangs.

However, there are a bunch of bullet cannons along the way, and some of them fire those evil homing bullets. But, you can keep them from firing at all if you're positioned on or next to them as they get very close to the clown car.
BGM: Sonic & Knuckles - Flying Battery Zone Act 1
MOON!!! Yes, this is what the springboard is for!
And that's it. I hope you all enjoyed watching me play Bowser Rampages Again! See you all later!
Nothing up there, I don't think...
Also, if it sounds like the music is only coming out of one speaker to you guys, that's because that's just how it sounds in the game for some reason.
Man, I am just obsessed with keeping this springboard with me, even though I think its usefulness has already come and gone...
Whoa! Holy crap! ...Wow, an evil homing bullet tried to get me at the last second, but I managed to avoid it!
Whoa, that was a risky move on my part.
I got kind of lucky there.
What are you? A Laser Brother? Be careful, because you can't spin jump off of the lasers, but you can destroy the lasers with a cape spin. (Think of the lasers as slow-moving baseballs.)
Oh, I just realized... Did I really just complete the entirety of "Mysterious Base..." without getting hit?! Holy cow. I think that's a first for me!
I had thought for a moment that maybe I'd be able to fry stuff in here, but these Boomerang Bros are in enclosed chambers that are neither flammable nor inflammable.
BGM: Cirno's Perfect Math Class (SMW custom music port)
Oh, there's a hidden 1-up here! Okay, let's go down the ladder now...

Also, just like with Cirno's autoscrolling area in Ninth Cave, if your reserve item is a feather, it's practically unretrievable here. (And actually, even a reserve mushroom or flower can be tough to retrieve here too, but they're more retrievable than a feather!)
And that's game, with 33 seconds to spare!
Ooh, a springboard. If I remember correctly, I'll want to take this with me so I can get something good in a moment!
Okay, I'm nearly done! I just have to make a few more jumps and reach Peach!
And, let's watch the credits roll...
Hmm... Can I time it so that I cape spin an exploding Bob-omb that I'm carrying so that it still injures Mouser but not me?
Now, this is a good place to use fireballs. (In fact, I should've switched power ups before I finished the previous room.)
Bah, the game stole my reserve flower... Alright, so we've got just 75 seconds to get outta here!
Moon count: 4
He's right. This isn't quite over yet!
Here what comes?
And, as that was not a pipe exit, my springboard is now gone.
Man, you're just as pathetic as before. Well, you do have pits in your room now, but you're still not all that difficult.
Okay, there's no Roto-Discs near this mushroom...
"Press up to continue"? Aww... This level isn't totally automatic...
I got sooo lucky there...
The cape is so good to have right there!
So much lag... May as well use it to assist me in my maneuvers.
BGM: CUSTOM - Bossin' Me Around by Spigmike
Soon to be taken over and deactivated by Mario.
Alright, it's mid-boss time! So, we meet again, Mouser...
Huh? I didn't get a bullet to the brain like I was expecting there? What is this madness?!
I wonder why the "THE END" is off center like that...
Whoa!
Wow, is it getting hot in here, or is it just me?
Possibly the hardest thing about the Mouser fights in SMW hacks is trying not to accidentally destroy the Bob-ombs before they blow up in Mouser's face!
This guy is just your ordinary run-on-the-mill Boomerang Bro. Nothin' special to see here.
I'm trying to remember if there are any hidden 1-ups or anything like that around here...
Note: This music was ridiculously loud compared to most of the other music in this hack, so I've reduced the volume of this portion of the video to spare your ears a bit.
Definitely jump up here where the flower power up is. While you're up here, the evil homing bullet cannon below won't fire, since it's off screen.
Okay, here I go with what I consider the trickiest part!
I'm glad that convenient "safe-from-tossed-shells" ledge was right there.
Uh, oh. Those undead duders are back.

However, just like with Cirno in Ninth Cave, you'll want to enter as caped Mario with a mushroom or flower in your reserve slot. If you get here with only capes, take an intentional hit in this room so that you can get a mushroom from one of the blocks.
To be continued...
Yep, I can totally do that!
And that's that! Now, let's proceed onward!

Oh, so we've got one of these battles again. It's definitely harder, with Bowser causing stunning quakes and firing tons of hammers now. But, you can certainly just tank a hit to beat him if you want (and if you're not small). However, you should still try to avoid taking damage if you can.
"Don't move"? Ooh, this is an automatic level!
Whoops! I actually intended to check for secrets up against the wall there, but I accidentally entered the pipe early. Oh, well. The firebar would've made secret-searching risky anyway.
Wow, not bad at all! Only two bullets were fired, and neither of them were evil homing bullets! Okay, just a little further and I'm done!
Alright, it's final boss time!
BGM: Final Fantasy IV - Boss Battle
Hey, it's WhiteYoshiEgg, the guy who likes to leave his mark all over the dirt tiles in the caves!
Honestly, I wish that both this area and the Cirno area were positioned higher on the screen so that grabbing your reserve item wouldn't be an issue during them...
Okay, I think one more hit ought to do it...
I forget if this springboard has any other major uses, but I may as well check.
Oh, but wait, there's more!
This so reminds me of a Metroid game...
Umm... I believe that cannon right there fires evil homing bullets. Let me just check that in a safe way...
BGM: Romancing SaGa 2 - Last Battle
Okay, it's time for me to take on Bowser's Mysterious Base...
I don't see any reason to take the lower path there...
BGM: Cave Story - Running Hell
Yep, evil homing bullets. Better be real careful of that.
Okay, so we've got an auto-scrolling sequence here, and Bowser and his clown car are basically made of munchers right now, so don't touch them.
Okay, now here's the deal. Both of these are feather blocks, and the final boss sequence starts on the other side of this door.
Hello, and welcome to the finale of Bowser Rampages Again! Now, let's see what the voting public has to say...
You're welcome! And now to press some other buttons while I'm holding right to exit...
There are some other familiar enemies in this place.
Nah, doesn't look like it...
If you can't safely prevent a cannon from shooting, just move on and try to destroy the bullet that appears ASAP, especially if it's an evil homing bullet.
Well, I guess I'll enter this level next...
Wow, I am really getting lucky with the close calls today.
That big firebar tried to ambush me, or something like that!
Oh, so ZMann wasn't important? Okay.
Try to keep most of the cannons from firing if you can to make your life easier.
